attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KHRi037LxRpC49kYttg_content
attribs.current: While flying, attack of opportunities against you or for you against others are at disadvantage

attribs.name: repeating_trait_-KHRi2uEhWSEdoH2hPfX_content
attribs.current: To use this speed, you cant be wearing medium or heavy armor, be encumbered, holding anything in your hands, and there must be at least 10feetx10 free space. At 1st Level you have the ability to Jump and Featherfall (use the spell effects as a pattern - target is obviously limited to youself only - the effects generated are non magical in nature) at will, At 3rd level you may spend 5ft of movement to you can jump up 10ft vertically and glide for 40ft until the end of your turn. At the start of your next turn you Land. If you start your glide from a height, your glide distance can be increased by 10ft for every additional 10ft you are off the ground. While gliding, any actions requiring your hands will cancel the glide and cause you to drop from your current position. At 5th level You have a flying speed of 50 feet, you speed 10 feet of movement to gain 5 feet of height, but you may spend 5 feet of altitude to gain 10 of movement.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZ8oHZ7fRF48Twx_content
attribs.current: Beginning at 1st level, while you are wearing no armor and not wielding a shield, your AC equals 10 + your Dexterity modifier + your Wisdom modifier.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZ9H5882ZY3HEdl_content
attribs.current:
Your practice of martial arts gives you mastery of combat styles that use unarmed strikes and monk weapons, which are shortswords and any simple melee weapons that dont have the two-handed or heavy property.
You gain the following benefits while you are unarmed or wielding only monk weapons and you arent wearing armor or wielding a shield:
You can use Dexterity instead of Strength for the attack and damage rolls of your unarmed strikes and monk weapons.
You can roll a d4 in place of the normal damage of your unarmed strike or monk weapon. This die changes as you gain monk levels, as shown in the Martial Arts column of the Monk table.
When you use the Attack action with an unarmed strike or a monk weapon on your turn, you can make one unarmed strike as a bonus action. For example, if you take the Attack action and attack with a quarterstaff, you can also make an unarmed strike as a bonus action, assuming you havent already taken a bonus action this turn.
Certain monasteries use specialized forms of the monk weapons. For example, you might use a club that is two lengths of wood connected by a short chain (called a nunchaku) or a sickle with a shorter, straighter blade (called a kama). Whatever name you use for a monk weapon, you can use the game statistics provided for the weapon.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZ9H5882ZY3HEdm_content
attribs.current: You can attack twice, instead of once, whenever you take the Attack action on your turn.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZAzqz-opwFbbTj_content
attribs.current:
Your training allows you to harness the mystic energy of ki. Your access to this energy is represented by a number of ki points.
You can spend these points to fuel various ki features. You start knowing three such features: Flurry of Blows, Patient Defense, and Step of the Wind. You learn more ki features as you gain levels in this class.
When you spend a ki point, it is unavailable until you finish a short or long rest, at the end of which you draw all of your expended ki back into yourself. You must spend at least 30 minutes of the rest meditating to regain your ki points.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZB7jHO14RthZad_content
attribs.current: Immediately after you take the Attack action on your turn, you can spend 1 ki point to make two unarmed strikes as a bonus action.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZCwR3avXOORHei_content
attribs.current: You can spend 1 kipoint to take the Dodge action as a bonus action on your turn.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZCwR3avXOORHej_content
attribs.current: You can spend 1 ki point to take the Disengage or Dash action as a bonus action on your turn, and your jump distance is doubled for the turn.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZCwR3avXOORHek_content
attribs.current:
Your speed increases by 10 feet while you are not wearing armor or wielding a shield. This bonus increases when you reach certain monk levels, as shown in the Monk table.
At 9th level, you gain the ability to move along vertical surfaces and across liquids on your turn without falling during the move.

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZCwR3avXOORHel_content
attribs.current:
You can use your reaction to deflect or catch the missile when you are hit by a ranged weapon attack. When you do so, the damage you take from the attack is reduced by [[d10 + @{dexterity_mod}[dex] + @{monk_level}[monk level]]].
If you reduce the damage to 0, you can catch the missile if it is small enough for you to hold in one hand and you have at least one hand free. Ifyou catch a missile in this way, you can spend 1 ki point to make a ranged attack with the weapon or piece of ammunition you just caught, as part of the same reaction. You make this attack with proficiency, regardless of your weapon proficiencies, and the missile counts as a monk weapon for the attack, which has a normal range of 20 feet and a long range of 60 feet

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZCwR3avXOORHem_content
attribs.current: You can use your reaction when you fall to reduce any falling damage you take by [[5 * @{monk_level}]].

attribs.name: repeating_classfeature_-KpUYEZDUcZGjnFqIBFT_content
attribs.current: You can interfere with the flow of ki in an opponents body. When you hit another creature with a melee weapon attack, you can spend 1 ki point to attempt a stunning strike. The target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or be stunned until the end of your next turn.
